SIMPLE: habited
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Habited
<hw>Hab"it*ed</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧b"⟦icr⟧t*⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>p. p. &
a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Clothed; arrayed; dressed; <as>as, he was
<ex>habited</ex> like a shepherd</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fixed by habit; accustomed.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>habited</qex> he was in sobriety.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Inhabited.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Another world, which is <qex>habited</qex> by the ghosts of men
and women.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Habitual</ent>⟦br⟧
